# Local CI gate before commit

Before creating a commit, run the checks below and confirm success.

## Gate trigger: code-impacting changes only

Run the **full CI gate** when staged changes are in:

- `apps/**`
- `packages/**`
- `scripts/**`
- `e2e/**`
- `.github/scripts/**`

Also require the full gate for root files: `package.json`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `pnpm-workspace.yaml`, `turbo.json`.

## Non-code changes (full gate not required)

Skip the full gate when staged changes are only in:

- `docs/**`, `*.md`
- `.cursor/**` (rules, skills, memory files)
- `.github/workflows/**` (targeted YAML validation only)

## Full gate

When code-impacting files are staged, run from repo root:

```bash
pnpm lint && \
pnpm typecheck && \
pnpm test:unit && \
pnpm build && \
pnpm test:integration && \
pnpm audit --audit-level=high
```

**Stack note (PRD §11, §17):** Turborepo fans out to `api` (Hono), `worker`, `web` (Next.js), `marketing`, `db`, `types`, `utils`. Unit/integration use **Vitest**. **Playwright e2e is not part of the local gate** — runs on `staging`/`main` in CI (PRD §11). Mark `n/a` only when a package legitimately has no such task yet.

## Integration tests — ephemeral containers only

Integration tests use **ephemeral Postgres + Redis containers** — not Neon, not a running `docker compose up` stack (PRD §11, Decision #38).

```bash
# ✅ CORRECT
pnpm test:integration

# ❌ WRONG — do not point integration tests at Neon or local compose
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://neon... pnpm test:integration
```

Optional ReportPortal locally: `phase run --env=CI -- pnpm test:integration` (DB/Redis still from ephemeral containers).

**Mandatory cleanup:** integration test scripts must tear down containers on success, failure, and interrupt.

## Enforcement

- If any full-gate command fails, **do not commit**. Fix failures first, then rerun from the start.
- After a full-gate commit, explicitly report that the full gate passed.
- Do not skip the full gate for code-impacting changes because failures are "likely unrelated".
